      "message": "For 32 bit platforms on API \u003c 21 we have access to pthread_cond_timewait_monotonic_np (and not to pthread_condattr_setclock, so using pthread_cond_timewait gives no guarantee about having a monotonic clock). On API \u003e\u003d 21 we have access to pthread_condattr_setclock which allows us to use pthread_cond_timewait with the guarantee that the clock will be monotonic.\n\nI am going to update this CL to define HAVE_PTHREAD_COND_TIMEDWAIT_MONOTONIC in this .cc file (since we are only using it here). This way we can stop relying on the Chromium definition through the build system (https://cs.chromium.org/chromium/src/build/config/android/BUILD.gn?l\u003d96\u0026rcl\u003d2b33f7e21ffa29e67a02d27161c0e03486287744, which looks temporary).",
